Chapter.Section:
Citing &YAGS;
If you publish a result and you used &YAGS; during your research, please cite us as you would normally do with a research paper:
C. Cedillo, D. López., R. MacKinney-Romero, M.A. Pizaña, I.A. Robles, R. Villarroel-Flores.
YAGS - Yet Another Graph System, Version &VERSION; (&RELEASEYEAR;)
http://xamanek.izt.uam.mx/yags/
@manual{YAGS, author = {Cedillo, C. and López, D. and MacKinney-Romero, R. and Piza{\~n}a, M. A. and Robles, I. A. and Villarroel-Flores, R.}, title = {YAGS - Yet Another Graph System, Version &VERSION;}, year = {&RELEASEYEAR;}, note = {http://xamanek.izt.uam.mx/yags/}, }
Several other citation formats can be obtained from the file YAGS-DIR/CITATION or by typing Cite("yags"); at the &GAP; prompt.
